.el .ds Aq '
.TH ox-clean 1  "ox-clean " 
.SH NAME
ox\-clean \- Clean outputs and cache
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBox\-clean\fR [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-cache\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-state\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-state\fR] [\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-file\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Clean outputs and cache
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be removed without deleting anything
.TP
\fB\-\-cache\-only\fR
Only clean cache entries
.TP
\fB\-\-state\-only\fR
Only clean state database
.TP
\fB\-\-state\fR
Delete the state database file entirely (recovery escape hatch for a corrupt state.db — it is a regenerable cache)
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Also remove the audit trail (runs and job history)
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Skip confirmation prompt
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Clear execution state even if live (non\-stale) sessions exist
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output JSON
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR [default: Oxymakefile.toml]
Oxymakefile path
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
